The Beck family, three generations strong, set out to harvest disease-free oysters after years of waiting for them to grow to legal size.
Managed reserves and oyster sanctuaries aim to boost oyster populations.
Concerns arise over introducing Asian oysters to the Chesapeake Bay, with calls for more research.
Cleanup efforts face challenges, with funding issues and slow progress.
The decline of native oysters and pollution threaten the bay's ecosystem.
Despite setbacks, oyster traditions and businesses like Harris's endure, preserving a vital part of Chesapeake Bay's heritage.
